pie: mannikim's personal image editor
===
provides `pie`, the image editor and `pcp`, a color picker program

features
- uses farbfeld as the image format. see https://tools.suckless.org/farbfeld
- stdin/stdout
- area selection
- simple terminal ui
- <2k loc

usage
---
use `pie -h` for usage

pie uses stderr for displaying a simple tui. this allows the program to
display text-based information without implementing font loading & rendering
to the program

pcp takes no arguments and always returns the selected color in the stdout

configuring
---
configure pie by editing the source code and recompiling

build
---
building requires a c99 compiler, libm, GLFW and GLEW

the compiler needs to support `__attribute__((always_inline))`, or you can
change the definition of the `ALWAYS_INLINE` macro in `common.h`

building

    make

install

    make install

branches
---
i made these branches because they implement features not required for the
base program and haven't completely stable api's yet

fifo: implements fifo-based ipc
attempt at making pie more modular
use /tmp/pie.fifo as the fifo path

uds: implements unix-domain socket-based ipc
made to replace fifo
duplex communication allows for better integration with other programs
use /tmp/pie.sock as the socket path
use `piec` to communicate with pie

issues: both are unable to run more than one instance at a time. a solution for
this is to add the process id to the name of the fifo/socket
for fifo this is a bit difficult to do since you need to sync the scripts with
the correct file for each instance. uds supports any filename via piec but pie
needs support for that yet

